WEBVTT

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:05.680
Last lecture we solved the sequencetose

00:00:03.040 --> 00:00:08.639
sequence bottleneck problem using the

00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:12.719
cross attention mechanism where we built

00:00:08.639 --> 00:00:16.000
an attention augmented RNN where the

00:00:12.719 --> 00:00:19.840
encoder RNN here processes the source

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:23.439
sequence to build a memory bank H1 to

00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:26.240
HT. The decoder RNN

00:00:23.439 --> 00:00:29.599
generates the target sequence

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:32.559
step by step. For example, here we are

00:00:29.599 --> 00:00:35.360
looking at the step T of the decoding

00:00:32.559 --> 00:00:38.559
where this cross attention

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:41.840
lets the decoder query the encoder

00:00:38.559 --> 00:00:46.239
memory to compute a dynamic context

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:49.360
vector CT. This solved the information

00:00:46.239 --> 00:00:50.960
bottleneck and improved the quality of

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:54.079
translation

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:57.680
dramatically. models could handle longer

00:00:54.079 --> 00:01:01.840
sequences and this approach became the

00:00:57.680 --> 00:01:04.239
state-of-the-art from 2015 to 2017. But

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:08.240
as you see here, still the encoding

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:12.000
process is sequential. We cannot compute

00:01:08.240 --> 00:01:15.280
HT until we have computed HT minus V.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.799
This makes parallelization during

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:21.600
forward pass impossible. And for

00:01:18.799 --> 00:01:24.720
sequences, it makes the training time

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:27.360
very long. And for sequences of size,

00:01:24.720 --> 00:01:29.840
hundreds or thousands of tokens, the

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:32.240
training time will be very long. And

00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:36.240
this sequential process means that uh we

00:01:32.240 --> 00:01:39.520
are not really utilizing our GPUs. and

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:41.759
the GPUs are mostly sitting idle waiting

00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:44.479
for this sequential computation to

00:01:41.759 --> 00:01:47.520
complete. Why this is important? Because

00:01:44.479 --> 00:01:50.079
if you remember the CNN architectures,

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:53.840
they are highly parallel and that's why

00:01:50.079 --> 00:01:57.759
we could scale it to handle very large

00:01:53.840 --> 00:02:01.600
data sets and that's what we want here

00:01:57.759 --> 00:02:04.240
also to be able to scale the learning.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:07.840
That's not possible here. As for example

00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:11.680
in the encoder uh if we want to process

00:02:07.840 --> 00:02:15.440
like let's say 100 uh token sequentially

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:20.000
we need 100 serial steps and if we want

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:23.920
to generate 80 tokens in the decoder we

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:27.040
need 80 serial step

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:30.959
which at total is

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:32.720
180 serial step per training example of

00:02:30.959 --> 00:02:35.519
course

00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:38.879
Um I mean you can think of parallelizing

00:02:35.519 --> 00:02:42.160
on the batch size but a batch is of size

00:02:38.879 --> 00:02:45.200
let's say 32 but our GPU has thousands

00:02:42.160 --> 00:02:47.040
of cores that will that will be vastly

00:02:45.200 --> 00:02:50.560
underutilized.

00:02:47.040 --> 00:02:53.360
So I mentioned that CNN's are great for

00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:55.840
I mean they are highly parallelizable

00:02:53.360 --> 00:02:58.239
and they excel in image processing

00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:59.920
because nearby pixels are highly

00:02:58.239 --> 00:03:02.159
correlated.

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:04.640
uh in other words they have uh strong

00:03:02.159 --> 00:03:06.640
local correlation

00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:09.840
uh but we know that text is difference

00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:12.879
and um the most critical relationship

00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:15.760
can span long distances

00:03:12.879 --> 00:03:19.360
so if we use a CNN for example for a

00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:22.239
sentence like the dog chase its tail and

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:26.319
if we want to use let's say

00:03:22.239 --> 00:03:28.879
local filters like this and we know that

00:03:26.319 --> 00:03:31.920
eventually we can see all of this

00:03:28.879 --> 00:03:34.720
relationship ship like this. For an

00:03:31.920 --> 00:03:39.120
important relationship like dog and

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:42.159
tail, we have to go up let's say like

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:45.040
this to meet

00:03:42.159 --> 00:03:47.840
and information must pass pass through

00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:51.440
many layers and this degrades the signal

00:03:47.840 --> 00:03:53.680
of course and we want to come up with a

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:58.959
different way of doing this encoding. So

00:03:53.680 --> 00:04:01.120
the idea that uh around 2017 was well we

00:03:58.959 --> 00:04:03.760
did the cross attention

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:06.080
and we came up with this general uh

00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:10.400
attention formula that we discussed last

00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:14.879
time. So in this uh attention mechanism

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:18.479
we get the queries from the decoder

00:04:14.879 --> 00:04:21.759
uh or the query side keys and values

00:04:18.479 --> 00:04:24.160
came from the encoder

00:04:21.759 --> 00:04:28.800
or the memory bank. But of course

00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:31.440
there's no requirement that Q K and V uh

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:34.880
come from different places. I mean they

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:38.320
can come from the same sequence.

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:40.000
for example the sequence X that we want

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:43.919
to encode.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:47.600
So the sequence is in R and D

00:04:43.919 --> 00:04:49.759
and we can form queries and keys and

00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:54.800
values from the same sequence. What I

00:04:49.759 --> 00:04:58.960
mean is basically Q is X WQ

00:04:54.800 --> 00:05:01.440
and each X is asking what am I looking

00:04:58.960 --> 00:05:04.880
for in my neighbors.

00:05:01.440 --> 00:05:08.639
So X for example X2 here looks at all of

00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:12.479
the neighbors and it's basically trying

00:05:08.639 --> 00:05:16.000
to see if there is a neighbor or

00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:17.600
neighbors that can improve its

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:21.520
representation

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:26.560
and add more context to it. Also the

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:29.199
same X provides keys and here he

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:32.479
basically means what

00:05:29.199 --> 00:05:35.440
do I offer to others and at the same

00:05:32.479 --> 00:05:39.280
time value?

00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:41.759
What information do I contain?

00:05:39.280 --> 00:05:44.800
So each position in the sequence can

00:05:41.759 --> 00:05:49.120
attend to every other position to gather

00:05:44.800 --> 00:05:52.240
context. Let's try this in a example. So

00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:55.840
consider a sentence. Let's say

00:05:52.240 --> 00:05:58.479
the bank by the river offers great views

00:05:55.840 --> 00:06:03.919
of the boats.

00:05:58.479 --> 00:06:06.960
And let's look at the bank position two

00:06:03.919 --> 00:06:08.720
and let's assume it acts like a query.

00:06:06.960 --> 00:06:12.000
What are my neighbors telling me about

00:06:08.720 --> 00:06:14.080
my meaning? It looks at the river and

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:15.919
the key of river is basically unrelated

00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:20.479
to water.

00:06:15.919 --> 00:06:23.440
looks at offers and the keys I might be

00:06:20.479 --> 00:06:25.280
a financial institution

00:06:23.440 --> 00:06:27.759
and boats

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:30.560
um which the keys again I'm related to

00:06:27.759 --> 00:06:33.039
water and the model computes attention

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:35.360
weights and there's a high attention to

00:06:33.039 --> 00:06:38.400
river and boats and low attention to

00:06:35.360 --> 00:06:40.960
offers let's say and it combines this

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:45.919
representations or values from these

00:06:40.960 --> 00:06:49.360
neighbors to basically add context to

00:06:45.919 --> 00:06:53.039
its meaning. So it realizes that oh this

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:56.319
is a river bank not a financial bank and

00:06:53.039 --> 00:06:59.120
it's crucial to note that this all

00:06:56.319 --> 00:07:01.919
happens within this sentence itself.

00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:05.280
Each word refineses its presentation by

00:07:01.919 --> 00:07:08.960
attending to related words. So that's

00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:12.400
how we update the embedding of each of

00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:16.560
these words or tokens and uh we can

00:07:12.400 --> 00:07:19.520
encode them and when we want to do the

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:22.479
decoding in an auto reggressive way

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:25.440
we're looking at the previous so let's

00:07:22.479 --> 00:07:28.880
say we have a word here that we want to

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:32.560
predict we look at the all previous

00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:35.599
words and query them to update it uh the

00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:39.280
meaning of that or predict that uh note

00:07:35.599 --> 00:07:43.840
that during the training we may have the

00:07:39.280 --> 00:07:48.560
future tokens also which we have to mask

00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:51.199
uh to not let the model cheat by

00:07:48.560 --> 00:07:54.960
querying them. So this is called causal

00:07:51.199 --> 00:07:58.400
masking which we will see in the code.

00:07:54.960 --> 00:08:01.039
Okay. So with that let's go uh back to

00:07:58.400 --> 00:08:04.319
this scale.

00:08:01.039 --> 00:08:08.720
uh attention and just review that one

00:08:04.319 --> 00:08:11.120
more time and then uh using that we can

00:08:08.720 --> 00:08:14.479
reddesign this encoder decoder

00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:16.960
architecture with self attention and

00:08:14.479 --> 00:08:20.160
cross attention fully and we drop we

00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:25.599
want to drop anything else that is for

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:29.680
example uh related to RNN or CNN. So

00:08:25.599 --> 00:08:35.360
again given a input sequence X

00:08:29.680 --> 00:08:37.919
and this is in R let's say N by D

00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:42.880
each sequence has n tokens and each

00:08:37.919 --> 00:08:46.399
token has a D dimension. So this uh

00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:49.279
dimension here is important somehow

00:08:46.399 --> 00:08:50.959
tells us what is the dimension of the

00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:52.560
representation for each one of these

00:08:50.959 --> 00:08:56.080
tokens

00:08:52.560 --> 00:08:59.839
and uh we call this the model. We will

00:08:56.080 --> 00:09:05.120
project them to this q k and v spaces.

00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:08.320
So q is x wq which

00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:11.360
projects x to this query space.

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:14.800
Same for keys and values.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:18.000
So note that uh the Q space Q and K are

00:09:14.800 --> 00:09:20.640
in the same size because they want to

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:22.959
look for their similarity but the value

00:09:20.640 --> 00:09:26.399
space is not necessarily at the same

00:09:22.959 --> 00:09:30.480
dimension. So that's why we call it DV.

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:34.800
That means that WQ and W K have the have

00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:37.040
similar dimension of D model

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:43.040
by DK.

00:09:37.040 --> 00:09:47.200
WV has dimension of D model DV. Then we

00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:50.320
compute the attention scores

00:09:47.200 --> 00:09:54.320
using this scale dotproduct

00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:57.279
which is a square matrix.

00:09:54.320 --> 00:10:00.720
And the entry I of I and J of this

00:09:57.279 --> 00:10:04.240
matrix measures how much position I

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:06.959
should attend to position J.

00:10:04.240 --> 00:10:11.360
And then we apply the soft max. So if

00:10:06.959 --> 00:10:14.560
this is step one, two, three, here we

00:10:11.360 --> 00:10:17.279
apply softmax to get attention weights

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:19.600
which is the same size and each row sums

00:10:17.279 --> 00:10:21.360
to one uh giving a probability

00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:25.040
distribution over positions to attend

00:10:21.360 --> 00:10:27.200
to. And that basically led us to the

00:10:25.040 --> 00:10:29.760
weighted combination of all of these

00:10:27.200 --> 00:10:33.760
values or the output that we are looking

00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:35.519
for which is attention weights multiply

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:40.079
by V.

00:10:35.519 --> 00:10:44.640
So given that what's the self attention

00:10:40.079 --> 00:10:48.880
of X? It's basically soft max of the

00:10:44.640 --> 00:10:53.120
dotproduct of X WQ

00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:56.000
and X W K. Here we have a transpose and

00:10:53.120 --> 00:10:59.680
then X WV.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:04.720
Okay. So let's look closely at this

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:07.519
um few observation. We don't care about

00:11:04.720 --> 00:11:10.079
u the order. Everything attends to

00:11:07.519 --> 00:11:12.720
everything. So even if we shuffle the

00:11:10.079 --> 00:11:16.240
input, the output shuffles in the same

00:11:12.720 --> 00:11:18.720
